HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 408
By Capley
A RESOLUTION to honor and recognize Adisyn "Adi" Runyon,
2025 Top Ten Senior of Hampshire Unit School.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to pay
tribute to those students who, through their natural talents and unflagging commitment to
academic excellence, have distinguished themselves in the classroom; and
WHEREAS, Adisyn "Adi" Runyon is one such exceptional student, who was recently
named a Top Ten Senior of the 2025 graduating class at Hampshire Unit School; and
WHEREAS, through diligent study, steady composure during examinations, and
steadfast commitment of time and talent, Ms. Runyon has achieved outstanding academic
success and joined the ranks of the best and brightest students in Tennessee and our country;
and
WHEREAS, in her remarkable high school career, Adi Runyon has earned an exemplary
grade point average while participating in numerous extracurricular activities, including
volleyball, basketball, Beta Club, FCA, and FFA; and
WHEREAS, her time at Hampshire Unit School saw her volunteer generously to help
with Little Hawks Basketball, Hampshire's Thanksgiving Lunch, and the middle school's
volleyball team; and
WHEREAS, apart from her superlative scholastic work, she has already exhibited her
extraordinary industriousness as a delegate to Girls State in 2024; and
WHEREAS, Adi Runyon's display of intellectual aptitude and ambition surely bodes well
for her future success at the University of Tennessee at Martin, where she will study physical
therapy; and
